cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modeling and named entity recognition. The use of external knowledge bases and the unsupervised learning approach also suggest that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval and natural language processing, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) respectively.
